&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;iCaSH (Integrated Contraception &amp; Sexual Health Services) &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 2 Clinic Assistant (iCaSH Norfolk)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cambridgeshire Community Services NHS Trust provides Integrated Contraception &amp; Sexual Health (iCaSH) across Bedfordshire, Cambridgeshire, Peterborough, Milton Keynes, Norfolk and Suffolk.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The appointment is to the join the iCaSH Norfolk team, as a Band 2 Clinic Assistant, 26 hours a week, on a 6 month fixed term contract.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Norfolk services are community based with level 3 hubs in Norwich, Great Yarmouth and King’s Lynn. Services provide one stop integrated clinical models of care to specifically meet the sexual and reproductive health needs of the diverse population.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will predominantly work as member of the Norwich administration team, providing front of house reception and call taking duties, administrative support and also support the clinical teams on occasion with clinical services running over six days a week (Monday to Saturday), including some evening service provision.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For part time posts - salary will be pro-rata.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information about the post, please contact&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ruth Bescoby&lt;/p&gt;
